After some further research, I believe there is no &quot;built in&quot; direct way to accomplish something like this.

**My current solution is the following:&lt;br&gt;**
*The base protocol:*
```swift
protocol Graph {
  associatedtype N:GraphNode

  // ... other functions
}

protocol GraphNode {
  var id: Int { get }
}
```
*Another protocol containing the function dependent of the type of the associatedtype:*
```swift
protocol RemovableNodes where Self:Graph, N:Equatable  {
    mutating func removeNode(_ node: N)
}
```

*Now we can provide a basic implementation:*
```swift
class InMemoryGraph&lt;N: GraphNode&gt;: Graph {
  // blablabla here goes basic implementation for all defined functions
}
```
*and an extension for the basic implementation if N:Equatable:*
```swift
extension InMemoryGraph:RemovableNodes where N:Equatable {
  func removeNode(_ node: N) {
    // implementation goes here
  }
}
```

